                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border border-gray-200">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 font-lora">World State</h3>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">Puzzles</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">The world contains obstacles, like locked doors or chasms, that require specific items from the player's inventory to overcome. This encourages exploration and problem-solving.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">Inventory</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">The player carries a collection of items. Managing this inventory is key to solving puzzles and progressing through the game.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">State Management</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">The game remembers every change: a door unlocked, an item taken, a character spoken to. This ensures the world feels persistent and responsive to the player's actions.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="structure" class="py-16">
            <div class="text-center mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Game Data Structure</h2>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">This section provides a look under the hood at how the game world is built. The entire world is defined in a single, large data structure (a Python dictionary). This approach makes it easy to add new rooms, items, and puzzles. Below is an example of one room's data.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="code-block p-6 rounded-lg shadow-lg max-w-4xl mx-auto overflow-x-auto">
<pre><code><span class="code-comment"># The 'world' is a dictionary of room objects</span>
<span class="code-key">'whispering_woods_entrance'</span><span class="code-punc">: {</span>
    <span class="code-key">'name'</span><span class="code-punc">:</span> <span class="code-string">"Entrance to the Whispering Woods"</span><span class="code-punc">,</span>
    <span class="code-key">'description'</span><span class="code-punc">:</span> <span class="code-string">"A path leads deeper into the woods to the north..."</span><span class="code-punc">,</span>
    <span class="code-key">'exits'</span><span class="code-punc">: {</span><span class="code-key">'south'</span><span class="code-punc">:</span> <span class="code-string">'meadowbrook_square'</span><span class="code-punc">,</span> <span class="code-key">'east'</span><span class="code-punc">:</span> <span class="code-string">'glimmering_caves'</span><span class="code-punc">},</span>
    <span class="code-key">'items'</span><span class="code-punc">: [],</span>
    <span class="code-key">'characters'</span><span class="code-punc">: [],</span>
    <span class="code-key">'puzzles'</span><span class="code-punc">: {</span>
        <span class="code-key">'east'</span><span class="code-punc">: {</span>
            <span class="code-key">'locked'</span><span class="code-punc">:</span> <span class="code-key">True</span><span class="code-punc">,</span>
            <span class="code-key">'key'</span><span class="code-punc">:</span> <span class="code-string">'iron key'</span><span class="code-punc">,</span>
            <span class="code-key">'message_locked'</span><span class="code-punc">:</span> <span class="code-string">"The gate is locked."</span>
        <span class="code-punc">}</span>
    <span class="code-punc">}</span>
<span class="code-punc">}</span></code></pre>
            </div>
        </section>

